KnownLibraries.Name: FreeRTOS
KnownLibraries.Author: Richard Berry <info@freertos.org>
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Real Time Operating System implemented for AVR (Uno, Leonardo, Mega).
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The primary design goals are: Easy to use, Small footprint, Robust. Uses Watchdog Timer for 15ms resolution. Slow blink = stack overflow. Fast blink = heap malloc() failure.

KnownLibraries.Name: Temboo
KnownLibraries.Author: Temboo
KnownLibraries.Sentence: This library enables calls to Temboo, a platform that connects Arduino/Genuino boards to 100+ APIs, databases, code utilities and more.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Use this library to connect your Arduino or Genuino board to Temboo, making it simple to interact with a vast array of web-based resources and services.

KnownLibraries.Paragraph: VS1003 and VS1053 MP3, MP3 player and recorder

KnownLibraries.Name: OneWireSTM
KnownLibraries.Author: Various - updated for STM by Roger Clark

KnownLibraries.Name: Ethernet_STM
KnownLibraries.Author: WIZnet :: Ported to STM32 by Vassilis Serasidis.
KnownLibraries.Maintainer: WIZnet and Vassilis Serasidis (for porting to STM32)
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables network connection (local and Internet) using the Arduino Ethernet board or shield. For all Arduino boards.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: With this library you can use the Arduino Ethernet (shield or board) to connect to Internet. The library provides both Client and server functionalities. The library permits you to connect to a local network also with DHCP and to resolve DNS.

KnownLibraries.Name: USBComposite
KnownLibraries.Author: Various
KnownLibraries.Sentence: USB HID / MIDI / mass storage library for STM32F1
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: USB HID / MIDI / mass storage library for STM32F1

KnownLibraries.Name: STM32duino_Examples
KnownLibraries.Author: several
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Provides several examples for the Arduino core for STM32 MCUs.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Arduino STM32 core, libraries and examples are available here: https://github.com/stm32duino

KnownLibraries.Name: LiquidCrystal
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino, Adafruit
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows communication with alphanumerical liquid crystal displays (LCDs).
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: This library allows an Arduino/Genuino board to control LiquidCrystal displays (LCDs) based on the Hitachi HD44780 (or a compatible) chipset, which is found on most text-based LCDs. The library works with in either 4 or 8 bit mode (i.e. using 4 or 8 data lines in addition to the rs, enable, and, optionally, the rw control lines).

KnownLibraries.Name: Firmata
KnownLibraries.Author: Firmata Developers
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables the communication with computer apps using a standard serial protocol. For all Arduino/Genuino boards.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The Firmata library implements the Firmata protocol for communicating with software on the host computer. This allows you to write custom firmware without having to create your own protocol and objects for the programming environment that you are using.

KnownLibraries.Name: Serasidis_XPT2046_touch
KnownLibraries.Author: Vasillis Serasidis.
KnownLibraries.Sentence: A simple XPT2046 Touch screen driver
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: A simple XPT2046 Touch screen driver

KnownLibraries.Author: Roger Clark,Nicholas Zambetti,Todd Krein,Perry Hung,Barry Carter,Donna Whisnant
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows the communication between devices or sensors connected via Two Wire Interface Bus.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Allows the communication between devices or sensors connected via Two Wire (I2C) Interface Bus.  Includes both Master and Slave drivers for both Hardware I2C ports of STM32F1 micros.
